The defendant Carter R Wilimovsky was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possess/Illegally Obtained Prescription [Modifiers: PTAC], an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 450.11(7)(h).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

miscConds.notes: $243 to be collected by the Dept of Corrections.  Court financial obligations shall be paid at the rate of 25% of the prison wages and work release funds. The balance remaining at release from prison be paid as a condition of extended supervison or parole at a rate determined by the supervising agent.  $200 DNA surcharge remitted.

Court finds defendant eligible for expunction under 973.015 no new crimes, ATR's, successful completion of probation.
Defendant shall complete a risk and needs assessment and comply with care plan goals related to prioritized need areas identified. Defendant advised of requirement to provide DNA sample.
